#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.89"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.89:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:0.2"
msgid "9. Channavagga"
msgstr "9. With Channa"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.89:0.3"
msgid "89. Bāhiyasutta"
msgstr "89. With Bāhiya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā bāhiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno "
"kho āyasmā bāhiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Bāhiya went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.89:1.2"
msgid ""
"“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato "
"dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’"
"ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bāhiya, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Bāhiya? "

msgctxt "sn35.89:2.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:3.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:5.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn35.89:6.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.64"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:7.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:8.1"
msgid "“Rūpā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are sights …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:9.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.89:9.2"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "eye consciousness …"

msgctxt "sn35.89:9.3"
msgid "cakkhusamphasso … pe …"
msgstr "eye contact …"

msgctxt "sn35.89:9.4"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind "
"contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:10.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:11.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:12.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn35.89:13.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:14.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ passaṃ, bāhiya, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi "
"nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, "
"sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with "
"the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye "
"contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.89:15.2"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … "
"painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind "
"contact."

msgctxt "sn35.89:15.3"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn35.89:15.4"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.89:16.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā bāhiyo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"And then Venerable Bāhiya approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He "
"got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping "
"him on his right, before leaving."

msgctxt "sn35.89:16.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā bāhiyo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto "
"nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, "
"tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Bāhiya, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon "
"realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived "
"having achieved with his own insight the goal for which people from good "
"families rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "sn35.89:16.3"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "sn35.89:16.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā bāhiyo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Bāhiya became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.89:16.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
